**How to test out the system :** 

**Step 1:** Download the file above and run it.

**Step 2 :**  
![][image1]  
Click this dropdown at the top left and click server & clients

**Step 3:**  
![][image2]  
Make sure this bar which is next to server & clients is set to 2 or 3

**Step 4:**  
![][image3]  
Click play

**Step 5:**  
Go to the screen holding Player1 (as of now this is the only player with admin commands you can change it later in your game.) Their name will be bold  
![][image4]

**Step 6**: Click G to enter ghost mode, click f to fly while in ghost mode (Player 1 only: Click right shift to open admin panel).

**Step 7:** While in ghost mode on player1, look at the client view of say player2 or player 3 and look at the spot player1 is in, you will see there is no trace of player1 at all, nothing.

**Step 8:** go in the admin panel on 1 and click player2 then grant ghost priveleges  
![][image5]

**Step 9:**   
You will now see player 2 can see player1 in ghost form and so can player1.  
Now when you go to player3 view they see literally nothing  
![][image6]  
![][image7]

**Step 10:**  
While in the admin panel if you click force ghost, the person who was forced into ghost will be put into ghost mode but will not be able to exit ghost mode, they will be able to fly though.

**Step 11:**  
A player set as a viewer will be able to see a ghost (they will be semitransparent) , test it by making player 1 a ghost and player 2 a viewer by clicking player 2 and clicking “Grant Viewer”.  
![][image8]

**Things to note about the program :** 

1. I have accounted for people using abilities in ghost mode, to counteract it I have disabled all other inputs except for mouse, movement, g and f  
     
2. I have tried to disable raycast and ontouch for ghost characters so players don't do stupid stuff and bug them out or hit them while they can't be seen  
     
3. The ghost models are non-collidable with players so players not only cant see them but cant touch them at all (0 trace they are there for the players)  
     
4. I made sure when a player is killed or reset in ghostmode their mode is taken away and they are forced out of ghostmode to prevent bugging

5. I have not eliminated all bugs, I'm sure there's loopholes, but like I counteracted most obvious ones.

6. I made this easy to install so you wont have a hard time plugging it in, and hopefully it works inside the game, it works in the test server fine.

7. All viewers will be able to see all ghosts. I could have made it different, but for simplicity I made it this way which I'm sure is fine.

**How to add it into your game :**

**Step 1 :**   
Copy this folder and put it into ReplicatedStorage.  
![][image9]

**Step 2 :**  
Copy this folder and put it into ServerScriptService  
![][image10]

**Step 3 :**  
Copy this folder and put it into StarterPlayerScripts  
![][image11]

**Step 4 :** 

Open AdminGhostServer (inside of GhostService folder)  
**![][image12]**  
Find ADMIN\_USER\_IDS  
![][image13]  
And input user ids that you want to add as admin, for example mine would be this (-1 is what i put in there for now as Player1 when we tested it out) **PS : MAKE SURE YOU PUT THE ID IN THERE THEN COMMA\!**  
![][image14]

**Things a little rough with the program :**

Only 1 thing, I have a visibility issue sometimes applied to players, if it happens (not common but can happen) they just need to reset, but usually it just happens to the server so it should be fine (maybe) its not a big deal but let it be known.
